results.name: Let qf(a,q) = Product_{j >= 0} (1-a*q^j); g.f. is qf(q,q^4)/qf(q^3,q^4).
formula: O.g.f.: A(x) = F(x)/G(x) where F(x) = Product_{k >= 0} 1 - x^(4*k+1) (see A284313) and G(x) = Product_{k >= 0} 1 - x^(4*k+3) (see A284316).
Continued fraction representations: A(x) =  1 - x/(1 + x^2 - x^3/(1 + x^4 - x^5/(1 + x^6 - ... ))).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 09 2005
